descript.abstract: This data set portrays labor statistics annual averages for the years 2005 to 2009, shown by county, for the United States and Puerto Rico. The data set was created by merging data from the Bureau of Labor Statistics with a file showing year 2001 county boundaries. Included is the total labor force, the number of employed and unemployed, and the unemployment rate for each county.
descript.purpose: These data are intended for geographic display and analysis at the national level, and for large regional areas. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:2,000,000-scale data. No responsibility is assumed by the National Atlas of the United States in the use of these data.

procstep.procdesc:
Year 2005-2009 labor statistics were downloaded from the Bureau of Labor Statistics as an Excel file. The file was loaded to ArcMap, then an attribute field was added and populated with the 5-digit FIPS code for each county.
The 2001 County Boundaries file from the National Atlas was edited to removed polygons associated with the U.S. Virgin Islands and polygons with no county designation (water areas). The edited county boundaries file was joined to the 2005-2009 labor statistics Excel table and the result saved as a new file. Unnecessary attribute fields were deleted and fields were renamed as necessary.
